data.description: Nestled in the serene Piney Creek neighborhood of Bastrop, this stunning home is just a 5-minute drive from downtown, offering both convenience and tranquility. Boasting a welcoming 9-foot ceiling and a ceiling fan in every bedroom, this residence exudes comfort. The upgraded 8-foot door adds an elegant touch, and the primary bedroom features an extra en-suite with an extended area for added luxury. Upstairs, a second living room awaits, perfect for relaxation or entertainment. The chef's kitchen is a culinary haven, complete with USB plugs throughout the home and Ethernet drops for seamless connectivity. Enjoy movie nights with the pre-wired surround sound system, and stay cozy by the wood-burning fireplace in the combined dining room and living area. The expansive quarter-acre backyard offers privacy and backs onto a lush greenbelt with captivating views. Plus, for outdoor enthusiasts, Fisherman's Park is just a 15-minute walk away, where you can indulge in swimming, water sports, basketball, tennis, volleyball, and city-hosted festivals. The park also features a splash pad for kids, a skate park, and a playground. Additional highlights include a shower-tub combo, Silestone countertop, a spacious 3-car garage, and a brand-new water softener. Abundant natural light throughout the house accentuates the extra-large pine trees and the generously-sized game room. This exceptional property combines comfort, style, and natural beauty while offering a vibrant community lifestyle – schedule your viewing today to experience it for yourself!
